  3. Revert = delete the generated `AGENTS.md` and unset the flag. Zero migration cost.

## Why mopsus, not the other candidates

- **agQSL**: filesystem-first, QSL-as-memory, explicit "do not rely on Claude auto-memory." An auto-generated `AGENTS.md` would conflict with the QSL doctrine — wrong test bed.
- **heated-debate**: too thin (one `shelley.ts`). `/init` would generate a near-empty file; no signal.
- **gaa**: read-only agent with `~/Code_2026/gaa/reports/` write fence; can't even commit the artefact.
